tourBios.exmtStatus: Conditionally Exempt / 72nd qualifier from Qualifying Tournament, Money List 61-100
tourBios.curYearHigh: At the Mexico Open, made his first career Web.com Tour cut. Made it to the weekend on the number (1-over), struggled to a 5-over 77 in the third round then rebounded with a 3-under 69 Sunday at El Bosque CC, including making his first career Web.com Tour hole-in-one on hole No. 12.
tourBios.carHigh: 2011: Made 11 starts but did not make a cut...Was one of nine players to make it through all four stages of the PGA TOUR Qualifying Tournament. Prior to 2011, had never competed on the Web.com Tour. Has never made a PGA TOUR start. 2010: Led the 2010 Peach State Professional Golf Tour by virtue of three wins and 16 top-10 finishes in 23 events. 2009: Was the medalist at the U.S. Open Qualifier...Played on the Hooters Tour and Peach State Professional Golf Tour.
tourBios.otherCarHigh: Walked on to the Auburn golf team for one season...Attended Robert E. Lee High School. Was all-city and all-state his junior year.
tourBios.personal: Has one sister...Began playing golf at age 17.
tourBios.otherInfo: Walked on at Auburn University. Began playing golf at the age of 17-years old. Was the medalist in the 2009 U.S. Open Qualifier.

dyn.dynResults: His best finish on the Web.com Tour was T47th in 2012 at the Price Cutter Charity Championship Presented by Dr Pepper.
dyn.dynStats: He ranks T32nd in Consecutive Cuts on the Web.com Tour.
